.B summary
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tatr
is a task tracker utility tooling. It enables the end-user to track the up-and-coming tasks to do. The tooling can create
.B new
tasks,
.B list
them using filters,
.B find
a task by its
.IR id .
The user can also
.B edit
a task also by its
.IR id ,
.B close
it,
.B delete
or
.B remove
it, or multiple at once.
.P
This tool is a replacement for the issue tracker that github has. Basically a, \&"Mom can we have Github's\&
.IR "issue tracker" ?
No, we have
.I "issue tracker"
\&at home.\|"\&
.P
Although, to note that this tool was original created by [@Tsoding](https://github.com/Tsoding).
.br
This is only my implementation of it, with added features, and adjusted to my liking.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B tatr help
.br
Shows the help message similar to this one.
.TP
.BI tatr\ init
.br
Initialises the
.I cwd
with a
.RI \|"tasks/"\|
directory, it does not yet exists.
.TP
.BI tatr\ find \ <task-id>
.br
Displays the information of a task, provided by its id.
.TP
.B tatr summary
.br
Displays general information about the tasks. Statistics relative to the tags and amount of tasks.
.TP
.BI tatr\ edit \ <task-id>
.br
Opens in your
.I $EDITOR
of choice the task provided by its id. Defaults to vim.
.TP
.BI tatr\ close \ <task-id> \ \&.\|.\|.\&
.br
Closes the task or tasks provided by their id.
.TP
.BI tatr\ rm \ <task-id> \ \&.\|.\|.\&
.br
Deletes the task or tasks provided by their id. Using
.BI tatr \ del
also works the same.
.TP
.B tatr\ ls\ [\|ls\ options\|]
.br
Displays every task answering to the query given by
.IR ls\ options \&.\&
.br
A query is formed of
.I \&.<tag>\&
and keywords. Keywords include
.BR and ,
.BR or ,
and
.BR not .
.br
Amongst tags, some are pre-defined by the tool, including:
.BR .all ,
.BR .OPEN ,
.BR .CLOSED ,
.BR .TAGGED ,
and
.BR .UNTAGGED .
.br
To note, an empty query defaults to
.BR .OPEN .
Adding to it result in
.BI .OPEN\ and \ <query> ,
unless otherwise specified
.BR .all ,
or
.BR .CLOSED \ tags.
.TP
.BI tatr\ new\ \-t \ <tag>,\&.\|.\|.\& \ \-p \ <int>\ "title"
Creates a new task of title
.IR "title" .
.br
.I new options
allow you to add comma seperated tags, and to define the task's priority as it's being created.
.SH Examples
.TP
tatr new -t feature,debug "this is a feature to be added for debug purposed" -p 42
.br
Creates a task named "this is a feature to be added for debug purposed" of priority 42 with the tags feature and debug.
.TP
tatr ls .CLOSED and .feature
.br
Lists closed tasks having the feature tag
.TP
tatr ls .all and .debug
.br
Lists all opened and closed tasks having the debug tag
.TP
tatr ls .all and .debug or .feature
.br
Lists all opened and closed tasks having the debug or feature tags
.SH NOTES
To be noted that as of 2026-07-03, the filtering system still lacks enclosing with parenthesis and name filtering.
